      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(pi-runner): re-apply tool allowlist before prompt dispatch",
        "body": "Fixes #74377.\r\n\r\n## Summary\r\n\r\n- Telegram + direct Anthropic sends `tools: []` even when the runner builds 17 effective tools, so the agent emits `tool_use` as plain text. 100% reproducible.\r\n- `runEmbeddedAttempt` sets the allowlist once at session creation, but Pi's `_refreshToolRegistry` can re-run later and empty `agent.state.tools` before `session.prompt()`. Static analysis ruled out a name-mismatch hypothesis.\r\n- Re-apply the allowlist right before each `session.prompt()`. Idempotent. Raw model probes (which legitimately empty tools) are skipped.\r\n- Logic extracted into `ensureActiveToolsBeforePrompt` and unit-tested. Diagnostic warns when the wipe path is hit (so we know the bug was real) or when re-apply restores fewer entries than the allowlist (separate Pi-registry bug class).\r\n\r\n## Test plan\r\n\r\n- [x] `pnpm test src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/run/attempt.ensure-active-tools.test.ts` — 7/7 pass\r\n- [x] `pnpm test src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/` — 61 files, 807 tests pass\r\n- [x] `pnpm tsgo:core`, `pnpm tsgo:test:src`, `oxfmt --check` clean\r\n- [ ] **Live repro by @everafloors-cmyk** — pull branch, DM the bot with `tools.profile=coding`, confirm tool_use lands as real API blocks. A `[OPENCLAW_TOOLS_DIAG] active tools were empty at prompt dispatch; restored to N/N` log line confirms the wipe was the cause and the re-apply recovered.\r\n- [ ] `pnpm check:changed` in Testbox before merge\r\n\r\ncc @steipete for owner review.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/issues/74377\r\n",
